The police in Osun State has arrested three soldiers who allegedly invaded a police post in the Obelawo area, along Ikirun Road in Osogbo on Tuesday night to free their colleague and cultists in detention. SaharaReporters learnt the soldiers were at the station to free their colleague and some suspected cult members. File photo used to illustrate story. It was gathered that the soldiers have however been arrested by the Tactical Unit of Anti-Cultism set up by the state Commissioner of Police, CP Olawale Olokode. SaharaReporters learnt that the soldier who was detained by the police was responsible for calling on his colleagues to rescue him from police custody. Instead, they were overpowered, arrested, and taken to the State Criminal Investigation Department. Osun State Police Command spokesperson, SP Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident, saying, “The soldiers came to the station and behaved themselves in an unruly manner but they were not successful. Three of the soldiers have been arrested and investigation is ongoing at the SCID.”